            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl1_Label1"><p>Microsoft SQL Server is a database plenty of features regarding replication, mirroring and failover clustering. All of them are strategies and configurations whose purpose is, with different ways of acting, to make data always available to client applications, in case of crashes and disservices, or simply to replicate data in more geographic locations to increase accessibility and availability performances. In this tutorial we won&#8217;t [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl1_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/sql-server-merge-replication-ftp-guide-remote-database-synchronization/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
