        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl5_Label1"><p>Exchange Server 2016 has been around for two years now when this article is written, and it already hits its 7th cumulative update. As stated in Microsoft Technet article, Exchange Server 2016 has been made to be more scalable, more efficient in hardware utilization, and more effective in failure isolation compared to its predecessor. Changes [&hellip;]</p>
