            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl9_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/restore-exchange-server-using-windows-server-backup/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Restore Exchange Server using Windows Server Backup</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl9_Label1"><p>When restoring an Exchange server using Windows Server Backup (WSB) role, the administrator must ensure that the backup is an Exchange-aware VSS-based backup. Having an Exchange-aware VSS-based backup is important to minimize the issue that will occur upon restoring the backup. An Exchange-aware backup can only be created by using plugin WSBExchange that does not [&hellip;]</p>
